Captain Gary Michael Rose was honored with the Congressional Medal of Honor by President Trump at the White House. Rose, a medic for the Fifth Special Forces Group in the Vietnam War, was recognized for his heroic actions during Operation Tailwind in 1970. He risked his life to treat and save wounded soldiers, even when he was injured himself. Rose's bravery and selflessness in the face of danger were commended, and he was praised for his continued service to his community after leaving the military.